# Sales Performance Analysis Dashboard (Power BI)

## Overview
This project presents an end-to-end sales performance analysis using real retail transaction data. The objective was to provide management with clear visibility into revenue trends, product performance, and profitability through an interactive Power BI dashboard.

## Business Problem
The business lacked a centralized reporting solution to monitor sales performance, identify top and bottom-performing products, and track profitability across categories and regions.

## Dataset
- Global Superstore sales dataset
- Over 50,000 transaction records
- Includes sales, profit, products, categories, regions, and customer segments

## Tools & Technologies
- Python (Pandas, NumPy)
- Power BI
- DAX
- Excel / CSV

## Project Workflow
1. Data cleaning and preparation using Python
2. Exploratory data analysis to identify trends and performance gaps
3. Feature engineering and metric creation
4. Power BI dashboard development with interactive visuals
5. Insight generation and business recommendations

## Key Insights
- Sales show a consistent upward trend over time
- Technology is the most profitable category
- Furniture generates high sales but low profit margins
- Western Europe leads in both sales and profit
- A small number of products contribute disproportionately to total revenue

## Dashboard Pages
- Executive Overview
- Sales Trends
- Product Performance

